---
## 🧩 Implemented Models

### 🔹 MLP — Multi-Layer Perceptron

A fully connected neural network applied to the **Breast Cancer Wisconsin Diagnostic Dataset**.

**Task:** Binary Classification

**Concepts Explored:**
- Dense (Fully Connected) Layers
- Non-linear Activation Functions
- Backpropagation
- Binary Classification
- Feature Standardization
- Performance Evaluation Metrics

**Metrics Evaluated:**
- Accuracy
- Precision
- Recall
- F1-Score
- Confusion Matrix

---
### 🔹 CNN — Convolutional Neural Network

A convolutional neural network designed for image classification using the **Fashion-MNIST dataset**

**Task:** Multi-Class Image Classification

**Concepts Explored:**
- Convolution Layers
- Pooling Layers
- Feature Extraction
- Fully Connected Classification 
- Image Representation Learning

**Metrics Evaluated:**
- Accuracy
- Confusion Matrix

---
### 🔹 GAN — Generative Adversarial Network

A generative model composed of two competing networks:

- Generator
- Discriminator

The model is trained using the **MNIST handwritten digits dataset**.

**Task:** Image Generation

**Concepts Explored:**
- Generative Modeling
- Adversarial Training
- Image Synthesis
- Generator and Discriminator Optimization
- Unsupervised Learning

The training process periodically displays generated samples to visualize the evolution of the generator.

---
### 🔹 GNN — Graph Neural Network

A Graph Convolutional Network (GCN) implemented using **PyTorch Geometric**.

The model is trained on the **Cora Citation Network Dataset**.

**Task:** Node Classification

**Concepts Explored:**
- Graph Convolutional Networks
- Node Embeddings
- Graph Representation Learning
- Graph-Structured Data Processing

**Metrics Evaluated:**
- Accuracy
- Precision
- Recall
- F1-Score
- Confusion Matrix

This model demonstrates how neural networks can operate directly on graph-structured data instead of traditional tabular or image datasets.

